Pay in Installments
To initiate a Pay in Installments request, send an HTTP POST request to the below URL with the required parameters. It’s also mandatory to pass your Hubtel POS Sales ID in the endpoint. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://invoicing.hubtel.com/api/invoice/{POS_SALES_ID}/pay-in-installments
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
invoiceNumber	String	Mandatory	The invoice number associated with the created invoice. It must not be empty and should be a maximum of 20 characters in length.
customerName	String	Mandatory	The name of the customer for whom this invoice is being created.
callbackUrl	String	Mandatory	The callback URL expected to receive the final status of the payment.
customerPhoneNumber	String	Mandatory	The phone number of the customer. Customer will receive invoice via this number.
customerEmail	String	Optional	This refers to the email of the customer. Customer will receive invoice via this email.
hasTax	Boolean	Optional	This indicates whether tax will be added to the invoice.
IssuedBy	String	Mandatory	This refers to the person or staff creating the invoice.
createdBy	String	Mandatory	This refers to the person or staff creating the invoice.
dueDate	DateTime	Mandatory	This refers to the date due for payment.
isDefault	Boolean	Optional	This helps to indicate whether an invoice is a draft invoice or not.
note	String	Optional	This is a brief description about the invoice.
reminders	ArrayOfObjects	Optional	This helps send reminders to customers about making payment for the invoice created.
isBefore	Boolean	Mandatory	This indicates whether reminders should be sent before or after the due date.
days	Integer	Mandatory	This indicates the frequency at which the reminders should be sent.
items	ArrayOfObjects	Mandatory	This helps schedule the one-time payment.
description	String	Mandatory	A brief description of the payment being made.
quantity	String	Mandatory	The quantity of the items being purchased
unitPrice	Float	Mandatory	The cost for the item being purchased.

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
status	String	The description of response received from the Receive Money API that is related to the ResponseCode.
Data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the Invoice API.
InvoiceId	String	An invoice id generated and it is tied to the invoice
paymentUrl	String	A payee can make payment on the same page the request was made from with this URL.
message	String	A payee can make payment on the same page the request was made from with this URL.

