Auto Debit
This enables you to create an invoice for your customer to make payment where their balance is automatically debited subsequently for each installments. This is very similar to payment by installments, but with auto debit, the customer’s wallet is automatically debited when the time is due for payment.

To initiate an Auto Debit request, send an HTTP POST request to the below URL with the required parameters. It’s also mandatory to pass your Hubtel POS Sales ID for Auto Debit requests in the endpoint. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://invoicing.hubtel.com/api/invoice/{POS_SALES_ID}/auto-debit
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
invoiceNumber	String	Mandatory	The invoice number associated with the invoice being created. It must not be empty and should have a maximum length of 20 characters
customerName	String	Mandatory	The name of the customer for whom this invoice is being created.
callbackUrl	String	Mandatory	The callback URL expected to receive the final status of the payment
customerPhoneNumber	String	Mandatory	The phoneNumber of the customer
customerEmail	String	Optional	This refers to the email of the customer
hasTax	String	Mandatory	This indicates whether tax will be added to the invoice.
IssuedBy	String	Mandatory	This refers to the person/staff creating the invoice
createdBy	String	Mandatory	This refers to the person or staff creating the invoice
dueDate	DateTime	Mandatory	This refers to the date due for payment
isDefault	Boolean	Optional	This helps to indicate whether an invoice is a draft invoice or not
note	String	Optional	This refers to a description about the invoice
reminders	Object	Optional	This helps send reminders to customers about making payment for the invoice created
days	Integer	Mandatory	This indicates the frequency at which the reminders should be sent
isBefore	Boolean	Mandatory	This indicates whether the due date Is before or after the currentDate
firstPaymentAmount	Decimal	Mandatory	This is the initial amount the customer must pay
firstPaymentDueDate	DateTime	Mandatory	This is the due date for the first paymentAmount.
frequency	String	Mandatory	This refers to how you want to schedule the payment for the customer. The options are Daily, Weekly, Monthly and Yearly
items	ArrayOfObjects	Mandatory	This helps schedule the auto-debit payment.
description	String	Mandatory	A brief description of the payment being made.
quantity	String	Mandatory	The quantity of the items being purchased
unitPrice	Float	Mandatory	The cost for the item being purchased.

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
status	String	The description of response received from the Receive Money API that is related to the ResponseCode.
Data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the Invoice API.
InvoiceId	String	An invoice id generated and it is tied to the invoice
paymentUrl	String	A payee can make payment on the same page the request was made from with this URL.
message	String	A payee can make payment on the same page the request was made from with this URL.

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
POST /api/invoice/11684/auto-debit HTTP/1.1 
Host: invoicing.hubtel.com 
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic endjeOBiZHhza24=
Cache-Control: no-cache

{
  "invoiceNumber": "test2567",
  "customerName": "John",
  "customerPhoneNumber": "024000000",
  "customerEmail": "rse@gmail.com",
  "hasTax": true,
  "issuedBy": "John",
  "createdBy": "John",
  "dueDate": "2025-03-20T08:00:23.147Z",
  "isDefault": false,
  "callbackUrl": "https://webhook.site/40b08e13-05f2-4892-8709-fe379878e6be",
  "note": "Auto Debit test",
  "firstPaymentDueDate": "2025-03-18T11:50:23.147Z",
  "firstPaymentAmount": 0.50,
  "frequency": "Daily",
  "reminders": [
      {
          "days": 2,
          "isBefore": true
      }
  ],
  "items": [
      {
          "description": "Auto Debit test",
          "quantity": 1,
          "unitPrice": 1
      }
  ]
}

SAMPLE RESPONSE
200 OK

