Transaction Status Check
It is mandatory to implement the Transaction Status Check API as it allows merchants to check for the status of a transaction in rare instances where a merchant does not receive the final status of the transaction from Hubtel after five (5) minutes.

To check the status of a transaction, send an HTTP GET request to the below URL, with the invoiceID as a parameters.

It’s also mandatory to pass your POS Sales ID for Status Check requests in the endpoint. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://invoicing.hubtel.com/api/invoice/{POS_SALES_ID}/{invoiceId}/status-check
Request Type	GET
Content Type	JSON

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
GET api/invoice/11684/7w6wZymWZ2/status-check HTTP/1.1
Host: invoicing.hubtel.com
Authorization: Basic QmdfaWghe2JheXU6bXVhaHdpYW8pfQ==

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
message	String	The description of response received from the API that is related to the ResponseCode.
code	String	The response code of the API after the request.
data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the API.
paymentStatus	String	Status of the transaction i.e.: Paid In Full, Partly Paid or Pending.
paymentDetails	ArrayOfObject	Provides details about individual transactions.
id	String	The unique ID used to identify a Hubtel transaction.
amountDue	Float	The total amount the customer is expected to pay
amountPaid	Float	The amount paid.
dueDate	DateTime	This refers to the due date for the payment.
paymentDate	DateTime	This refers to the date the payment was made.
orderId	Float	Another identifier for the payment.
status	String	Indicates whether a particular transaction is Paid, Pending or Failed.
isWithinRetryWindow	Boolean	An indication on whether or not the payment can be retried.
retriedCount	Number	An indication on how many times the transaction had to be retried.
receiptNumber	String	The receipt Number associated with the payment. It can be null.

SAMPLE RESPONSE (Paid)
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
  "message": "Success",
  "code": 200,
  "data": {
      "paymentStatus": "Paid In Full",
      "paymentDetails": [
